Karan
The field of software engineering is continuously evolving, and advancements in artificial intelligence (AI) and automation are indeed impacting various industries, including technology. While AI has the potential to automate certain tasks traditionally performed by software engineers, it is also creating new opportunities and roles within the field.

It's important to note that AI is not expected to eliminate the need for software engineers altogether. Instead, it is likely to change the nature of the work, with engineers focusing more on designing and developing AI systems, creating algorithms, and solving complex problems.

AI can automate routine tasks like code generation or testing, but software engineering involves much more than just those tasks. Software engineers bring a range of skills, such as problem-solving, system design, software architecture, and collaboration, which are not easily replaceable by AI.

Avocado Pesto Pasta Recipe 🥑🌿🍝 *I eyeballed this but you can watch the amount I put in the video 🙌✨ Pasta Sauce Ingredients Basil Spinach Cashews Avocado Parmesan Cheese Lemon Juice Olive Oil Salt Pepper Sugar Steps : 1. Cook your pasta until done and combine together with the sauce 3. Season with salt and pepper with a little bit of sugar 4. “Friends you’ve had since childhood aren’t just a part of your life, they’re a part of you. For me, that’s Akshada. I met her in Junior KG & the 1st thing I noticed was the dimples on her cheeks. We’d sit together in class & talk so much that the teacher would change our places! And it wasn’t just at school – when we were 8 or 9 years old, we spent long hours talking over the landline & our parents got so irritated. As we grew up together, Akshada became my rock. Be it helping me in my studies or helping me through a tough time, she was always the 1 I turned to. In fact, a lot of experiences I’ve had in life wouldn’t have happened if not for her. It must’ve been the 9th grade & we both desperately wanted to have a night out. Since my parents were strict, I told her, ‘They won’t allow me.’ But she magically convinced them & we had a great night at a friend’s place. From studies to movies to trips, we did it all together. In 2017, we went on our first trip to Pune with our friends. We were climbing the Sinhagad Fort & I was feeling extremely weak. She simply held my hand & guided me through. With Akshada, I've never needed words, she just always got it, you know? Last year, when her UK visa was finalized, it finally hit us that we wouldn’t be there for so many important moments in each other’s lives. I even remember saying, ‘Tere bina birthday kaise celebrate karungi?’ With a heavy heart, I bid adieu to her last August. Of course, we kept talking over messages and video calls, but I’d continuously miss her presence. And then, a month ago, just as I was cutting my birthday cake, she came from behind & surprised me! I couldn’t believe my eyes! The girl had come down, all the way from the UK just for my birthday! The tears just kept flowing. And when I finally hugged her, I realised just how much I missed her. We spent an amazing week together– we watched movies, ate at cafés & I soaked up my days enjoying her company. Surprisingly this time, when she was leaving, I wasn't as overwhelmed. In fact, I knew our friendship could overcome anything. It’s a blessing to have good friends, but friends like her that become family–that’s a different ballpark altogether."
